{"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/PollableInputStreamRef\/skipAsync(count:ioPriority:cancellable:callback:userData:)","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"skipAsync","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"count","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Int","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si"},{"text":", ","kind":"text"},{"text":"ioPriority","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Si","text":"Int","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":", "},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"cancellable"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:3GIO14CancellableRefV","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/CancellableRef","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"CancellableRef"},{"text":"? = nil, ","kind":"text"},{"text":"callback","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"GAsyncReadyCallback","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@GAsyncReadyCallback"},{"text":"? = nil, ","kind":"text"},{"text":"userData","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"gpointer","preciseIdentifier":"c:gtypes.h@T@gpointer","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"? = nil)"}]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"text":"Discussion","type":"heading","anchor":"discussion","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"During an async request no other sync and async calls are allowed,"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"and will result in "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"pending"},{"text":" errors.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"A value of ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"count"},{"type":"text","text":" larger than "},{"code":"G_MAXSSIZE","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" will cause a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"invalidArgument"},{"type":"text","text":" error."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"On success, the number of bytes skipped will be passed to the callback."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"It is not an error if this is not the same as the requested size, as it","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"can happen e.g. near the end of a file, but generally we try to skip"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"as many bytes as requested. Zero is returned on end of file"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"(or if ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"count"},{"type":"text","text":" is zero), but never otherwise."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Any outstanding i\/o request with higher priority (lower numerical value)"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"will be executed before an outstanding request with lower priority.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Default priority is [PRIORITY_DEFAULT](\/\/documentation\/glib\/priority_default.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The asynchronous methods have a default fallback that uses threads to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"implement asynchronicity, so they are optional for inheriting classes."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"However, if you override one, you must override all."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"}],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"sections":[],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/PollableInputStreamRef","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/PollableInputStreamRef\/InputStreamProtocol-Implementations"]]},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Request an asynchronous skip of "},{"code":"count","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" bytes from the stream."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"When the operation is finis